reer%20pivots.%3Cp%3EMira%20Lane%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E's%20Mira%20Lane%20shared%20what%20information%20job%20seekers%20should%20collect%20before%20making%20a%20career%20pivot.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELane%20started%20out%20as%20a%20software%20developer%20and%20eventually%20created%20an%20AI%20prototyping%20lab%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20gathering%20insights%20from%20networking%2C%20internships%2C%20and%20research%20can%20help%20you%20make%20an%20informed%20choice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20executive%20Mira%20Lane%20is%20all%20for%20following%20your%20passions%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcisco-liz-centoni-career-transition-advice-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echanging%20your%20career%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20exactly%20what%20she%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20encourages%20approaching%20a%20career%20shift%20with%20a%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20people%20that%20are%20wanting%20to%20pivot%2C%20I%20would%20pivot%20with%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20senior%20director%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20Envisioning%20Studio%20at%20Google%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELane%2C%20who%20started%20her%20career%20as%20a%20software%20developer%20and%20went%20on%20to%20create%20an%20AI%20prototyping%20lab%20that%20explores%20the%20impact%20of%20tech%20innovation%20on%20society%2C%20said%20that%20many%20people%20switch%20careers%20multiple%20times%20because%20they're%20uncertain.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20job%20seekers%20should%20gather%20as%20much%20information%20as%20possible%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20career%20pivot%20they're%20making%20is%20the%20right%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20talking%20to%20people%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20watching%20YouTube%20videos%20about%20jobs%20that%20interest%20you%2C%20and%20trying%20out%20internships%2C%20Lane%20said.%20If%20you're%20earlier%20in%20your%20career%2C%20you%20should%20also%20try%20to%20choose%20a%20college%20that%20provides%20opportunities%20to%20gain%20work%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bconstantly%20get%20some%20feedback%2C%26quot%3B%20Lane%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20you're%20just%20starting%20out%20in%20the%20workforce%20or%20looking%20to%20make%20a%20shift%20mid-career%2C%20changing%20careers%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20common.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHowever%2C%20Lane's%20advice%20comes%20amid%20an%20ongoing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-worker-layoffs-career-poll-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworkforce%20transformation%20driven%20by%20AI%20advancements%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202025%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20survey%20found%20that%2041%25%20of%20companies%20globally%20expect%20to%20reduce%20staff%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years%20because%20of%20the%20new%20tech%2C%20meaning%20more%20people%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20adjust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20jobs%20are%20kind%20of%20evolving%20in%20this%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20Lane%20said.%20%26quot%3BEverything's%20kind%20of%20shifting.%20So%20you%20want%20to%20be%20in%20a%20space%20where%20you're%20getting%20a%20lot%20of%20signals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20how%20Lane%20navigated%20multiple%20career%20pivots.%20After%20starting%20her%20career%20as%20a%20software%20developer%2C%20Lane%20moved%20to%20program%20management%20and%20then%20later%20on%20transitioned%20to%20leading%20AI%20ethics%20and%20society%20at%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20nearly%20two%20decades%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20Lane%20saw%20an%20opportunity%20for%20companies%20to%20engage%20more%20directly%20in%20conversations%20about%20the%20tools%20they%20were%20developing.%20That%20inspired%20her%20to%20build%20a%20team%20of%20creative%20strategists%2C%20philosophers%2C%20and%20researchers%20focused%20on%20discussing%20technology%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20like%20when%20technology%20is%20built%2C%20and%20then%20people%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20decisions%20that%20were%20made%20that%20weren't%20really%20intentional%2C%26quot%3B%20Lane%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20visual%20artist%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELane%20said%20when%20she%20was%20at%20Microsoft%20and%20was%20%26quot%3Bpoking%20around%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20new%20role%2C%20she%20met%20the%20person%20who%20would%20eventually%20become%20her%20boss%20at%20Google.%20She%20said%20he%20asked%20her%20what%20she%20wanted%20to%20do%20with%20her%20life%20and%20caught%20her%20off%20guard%2C%20so%20she%20asked%20if%20she%20could%20get%20back%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20she%20had%20an%20idea%20of%20her%20interests%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Lane%20said%20it%20was%20important%20to%20pause%20and%20think%20about%20what%20she%20really%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20prepared%20to%20just%20answer%20that%20on%20the%20fly%2C%26quot%3B%20Lane%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%2C%20'if%20someone's%20asking%20me%2C%20let%20me%2C%20reflect%20on%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20some%20thought%2C%C2%A0Lane%20prepared%C2%A0a%20one-page%20pitch%20about%20the%20lab%20she%20wanted%20to%20create%2C%20which%20ended%20up%20becoming%20a%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELane%20said%20once%20you%20get%20enough%20signals%20about%20what%20you%20like%20or%20don't%20like%2C%20you%20should%20listen%20to%20what%20%26quot%3Blights%20you%20up.%26quot%3B%20If%20you%20find%20yourself%20following%20a%20path%20that%20doesn't%20make%20you%20excited%2C%20maybe%20it's%20not%20the%20right%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%2F%2Fembed.typeform.com%2Fnext%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-tf-live%3D%5C%2201K0FDNEGB0E