iety%20that%20flourishes%20in%20these%20conditions.%20It%20is%20called%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20Golden%20Sitaphal%20(Custard%20Apple).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENMK-01%20(Golden)%20is%20cultivated%20in%2016%20Indian%20states%20and%20even%20in%20Tanzania%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F458835%2Fcsir-neeri-eco-rejuvenation-technology-vidarbha-maharashtra-scientist-insights%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eespecially%20in%20dryland%20zones.%20Maharashtra%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20particularly%20drought-prone%20districts%20like%20Solapur%2C%20Beed%2C%20Aurangabad%2C%20and%20Parbhani%2C%20has%20seen%20widespread%20adoption%20of%20this%20variety%E2%80%94followed%20by%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F389465%2Fparmeshwar-thorat-avocado-organic-farming-drought-beed-maharashtra%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFarmers%20also%20praise%20its%20high%20yields%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20go%20up%20to%2010%20tonnes%20per%20acre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBut%20who%20developed%20the%20Golden%20Sitaphal%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20sat%20down%20with%2067-year-old%20farmer%20innovator%20Navnath%20Kaspate%2C%20the%20mind%20behind%20this%20unique%20variety.%20In%202019%2C%20his%20innovation%20earned%20him%20Intellectual%20Property%20Rights%20from%20the%20Protection%20of%20Plant%20Varieties%20and%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Rights%20Authority%20(PPV%26amp%3BRA).%20Today%2C%20he%20owns%20a%2070-acre%20farm%E2%80%94Madhuban%20Farm%20and%20Nursery%E2%80%94which%20is%20home%20to%2042%20different%20varieties%20of%20custard%20apples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETracing%20the%20history%20of%20Golden%20Sitaphal%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBelonging%20to%20the%20Annonaceae%20family%2C%20custard%20apple%E2%80%94heart-shaped%2C%20spherical%2C%20or%20irregular%E2%80%94features%20quilted%20skin%20that%20turns%20brown%20as%20it%20ripens.%20Originally%20from%20South%20America%20and%20the%20West%20Indies%2C%20Sitaphal%20was%20introduced%20to%20India%20by%20the%20Portuguese%20in%20the%2016th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarkably%2C%20depictions%20of%20custard%20apples%20appear%20in%20ancient%20Indian%20sculptures%2C%20such%20as%20those%20at%20Bharhut%2C%20Sanchi%2C%20Ajanta%2C%20and%20Mathura%2C%20dating%20back%20to%20the%202nd%20century%20BCE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20varieties%20like%20Balanagar%2C%20Phule%20Purandhar%2C%20and%20Lal%20Sitaphal%20exist%2C%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%20is%20expanding%20rapidly%20due%20to%20its%20strong%20market%20acceptance%20and%20profitability%20for%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EStarted%20by%20one%20innovator%2C%20many%20followed%20suit%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20dryland%20crop%2C%20custard%20apple%20requires%20minimal%20irrigation%E2%80%94especially%20in%20the%20first%20two%20years%E2%80%94and%20is%20well-suited%20for%20drip%20irrigation%2C%20resulting%20in%20fewer%20pest%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-500x375.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Golden%20Sitaphal%20farmer%20innovator%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-1536x1152.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-150x113.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470.jpg%201600w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476011%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EMany%20farmers%20and%20experts%20praise%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%20for%20its%20high%20yield%2C%20larger%20fruit%20size%2C%20fewer%20seeds%2C%20and%20better%20market%20prices.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaspate%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20used%20to%20grow%20grapes%20and%20ber%2C%20but%20after%20developing%20NMK-01%2C%20I%20converted%20my%20entire%20farm%20to%20Sitaphal%2C%20inspiring%20others%20to%20follow.%E2%80%9D%20Farmers%20in%20five%20talukas%E2%80%94Barshi%2C%20Khamgaon%2C%20Ghormale%2C%20Kasarwadi%2C%20and%20Wanewadi%E2%80%94took%20to%20the%20charm%20of%20custard%20apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Barshi%20taluka%20alone%2C%20140%20villages%20now%20cultivate%20custard%20apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20Is%20NMK-01%20Golden%20Sitaphal%20the%20most%20preferred%20variety%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20173%20accepted%20%3Cem%3EAnnona%3C%2Fem%3E%20species%20worldwide%2C%20Kaspate%E2%80%99s%2070-acre%20Madhuban%20Farm%20and%20Nursery%20is%20like%20a%20living%20museum.%20You%20can%20find%20%3Cem%3EAnnona%20glabra%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EPink%E2%80%99s%20Mammoth%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EAnnona%20muricata%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EIcecal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Jem%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EAnnona%20montana%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20many%20more%20on%20his%20farm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20farm%20is%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20largest%20nursery%20devoted%20to%20Sitaphal%20and%20also%20serves%20as%20a%20development%20and%20research%20centre.%20Additionally%2C%20he%20hosts%20prospective%20custard%20apple%20growers%20with%20free%20full-day%20workshops%20on%20agronomic%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20created%20around%203%2C000%20varieties%20using%20the%20process%20of%20cross-pollination.%20These%20cannot%20be%20found%20elsewhere.%20Only%20when%20one%20registers%20a%20variety%20with%20an%20authority%20like%20the%20PPV%20%26amp%3B%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Rights%20Authority%20(FRA)%2C%20can%20it%20be%20officially%20recognised.%20I%20have%20selected%20some%20of%20them%2C%20filed%20for%20patents%2C%20and%20started%20acquiring%20Intellectual%20Property%20Rights%20(IPR).%20In%20India%2C%20living%20things%20like%20plants%20and%20animals%2C%20and%20the%20natural%20processes%20used%20to%20produce%20them%2C%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20patented%E2%80%94but%20they%20can%20receive%20other%20forms%20of%20IPR%20protection%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolapur%E2%80%99s%20Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendra%20highlights%20several%20of%20his%20innovative%20custard%20apple%20varieties%3A%20Annona-2%2C%20NMK-1%2C%20NMK-2%2C%20NMK-3%2C%20and%20Finger%20Prints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Kaspate%E2%80%99s%20most%20popular%20varieties%20is%20NMK-1%2C%20which%20he%20began%20developing%20in%202002.%20Farmers%20love%20it%20for%20its%20attractive%20colour%20and%20size%2C%20the%20good%20number%20of%20fruits%20each%20plant%20produces%2C%20and%20its%20uniform%20shape%E2%80%94making%20it%20ideal%20for%20export.%20The%20fruits%20also%20stay%20unripe%20on%20the%20plant%20for%2020%E2%80%9325%20days%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20crack%20after%20harvesting%2C%20and%20suffer%20fewer%20losses%20during%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EComparing%20varieties%3A%20market%20research%2C%20pricing%2C%20yield%2C%20taste%2C%20and%20farmer%20preference%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaharashtra%20leads%20custard%20apple%20production%20in%20India%2C%20with%20other%20popular%20varieties%20like%20Lal%20Sitaphal%2C%20Balanagari%2C%20and%20Phule%20Purandhar%20also%20grown%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%2055%2C000%20hectares%20of%20custard%20apple%20farms%20in%20India%2C%207%2C000%20hectares%20are%20in%20Maharashtra%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECustard%20apples%20are%20traded%20daily%20in%20and%20outside%20the%20state%2C%20with%20supplies%20reaching%20markets%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20Pune%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20and%20Delhi.%20From%20market%20yards%20in%20Pune%20and%20Navi%20Mumbai%2C%20the%20creamy%2C%20grainy-fleshed%20fruit%20is%20distributed%20to%20fruit%20stalls%20and%20malls%20in%20major%20cities%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20Balanagar%20and%20Phule%20Purandhar%2C%20NMK-01%20yields%20up%20to%2012%20tonnes%20per%20acre%20(versus%20five%20to%20six%20tonnes)%20and%20commands%20a%20higher%20price.%20However%2C%20while%20its%20appearance%20and%20sweetness%20appeal%20to%20many%2C%20some%20growers%20and%20consumers%20find%20its%20flavour%20less%20desirable%20than%20local%20varieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20970px)%20100vw%2C%20970px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22970%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Golden%20Sitaphal%20farmer%20innovator%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465.jpg%20970w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753